Creating Applications and Load The Data 6

You are about to create a dashboard for the violent crimes in Chicago and this is what i should look like.

The following steps will instruct you on how to recreate the dashboard from start to finish.


We will start by opening Qlik Sense.

 

Creating Applications

1.         Click "Create New App"

2.         Name the application, we named it " Chicago Violent Crime Dashboard From 2016-Present "

3.         Click "Create" and then click "Open App"

4.         Download the attached Zip file to use as a starting point. Save the file to your computer or click on the link to go to the website to download the file from there https://catalog.data.gov/dataset/crimes-2001-to-present-398a4/resource/4c948605-0db4-45e8-9c06-c851f05f9f37?inner_span=True

Click on download and click on the downloaded file on the bottom left of your screen. Open the file and save it to your desired location.

5.         Now we need to load data to our report. Since the data is continuously updated, its best to load the data directly via the website instead of downloading the data file locally and loading the file from the locally saved file. PLEASE NOTE THAT THIS CAN TAKE SEVERAL MINUTES.

6.         Here are the steps required to load the data from the website:

a.     Click add Data

b.  Choose Web as data by clicking Web file

c.   Paste the website link for the data file: https://data.cityofchicago.org/api/views/ijzp-q8t2/rows.csv?accessType=DOWNLOAD  and name your connection like its shown below

d.     Once you got the connection you will see this

e.     Load the data by clicking "OK" and since it is a CSV file make sure you select comma separate, select all fields and click on add data.  Or download the last 5yrs from the attached folder also, load the population and Zip Code file.

f.   Or if you load the data from the attached file then click on my computer then to your excel file path and add Chicago crime, Population, and Zip file.

g.   a.     Make the association or relationships, between the tables you can use the recommended one or you can just drag and connect the files. Make sure the associations are matched with the proper Serial Key.

h.   Then Load the data.

Video: Introduction to Set analysis
